statement.p:
Let A = {\left\{1,2,3,4,5\right\}} \text{.} 




How many subsets of A are there? That is, find \newcommand{\pow}{\mathcal P}|\pow(A)|\text{.}






How many subsets of A contain exactly 3 elements?






How many subsets of A contain only even numbers?






How many subsets of A contain an even number of elements?

p.m:
\mathop{m C}
