solution.p:
Now all the ways to distribute the 20 units to the four y_i variables can be found using stars and bars, specifically 20 stars and 3 bars, so {23 \choose 20} ways. But this includes the ways that one or more y_i variables can be assigned more than 3 units. So subtract using PIE to get

\displaystyle{                {23 \choose 3} -\left( {4\choose 1} {16 \choose 3}-{4\choose 2} {9 \choose 3} + \dots \right)
              }

statement.p:
For each of the following, find the number of shortest lattice paths from (3,3) to (11,11) which: 




pass through the point (7,5)\text{.}






avoid (do not pass through) the point (9,7)\text{.}






either pass through (7,5) or (9,7) (or both).

