solution.p:
For each case, you must use the recurrence to find f(1)\text{,} f(2) ... f(6)\text{.}  But notice each time you just add 8 to the previous.  We do this 6 times. 




f(6) = 49\text{.}




f(6) = 55\text{.}




f(6) = 62\text{.}




f(6) = 304\text{.}

